# Portfolio Development Task Breakdown

## 1. Planning and Design System
- [ ] Define the core brand identity (colors, typography, vibe).
- [ ] Establish the tech stack (Next.js, Framer Motion, GSAP).
- [ ] Outline the site architecture (Home, About, Work/Case Studies, Contact).

## 2. Foundation Setup
- [x] Initialize the Next.js project.
- [x] Configure global styles and CSS variables for the color palette.
- [x] Set up layout components (Navbar, Footer, Custom Cursor).

## 3. Core Components (The "Vibe")
- [x] Implement smooth scrolling (e.g., Lenis).
- [x] Create reusable animated text components (reveal on scroll).
- [x] Build a dynamic, interactive hero section.

## 4. Page Implementation
- [x] **Home Page:** Hero, Featured Work showcase with hover effects, brief About snippet.
- [ ] **Work/Projects Page:** Grid or list of case studies with filtering.
- [ ] **Case Study Template:** Deep dive layout with rich media support, sticky navigation.
- [ ] **About Page:** Personal story, experience timeline, skills, interactive resume.
- [ ] **Contact Page:** Form, social links.

## 5. Polish and Optimization
- [ ] Refine micro-interactions (button hovers, link underlines, custom cursor states).
- [ ] Optimize images and videos for performance.
- [ ] Ensure responsive design across all devices (mobile, tablet, desktop).
- [ ] Accessibility pass (ARIA labels, contrast, keyboard navigation).
